WEBVTT

00:00.100 --> 00:03.700
WOMAN: And we're live in three, two...

00:03.750 --> 00:07.650
Marilyn Miglin started
her career as a dancer

00:07.700 --> 00:10.950
at the legendary Chez Paree
nightclub in Chicago.

00:11.000 --> 00:12.800
- Many years ago.
- [laughs]

00:12.850 --> 00:14.950
But performing under those
bright stage lights,

00:15.000 --> 00:17.100
she found that her makeup
was always running.

00:17.150 --> 00:19.700
And that's how your interest
in cosmetics began.

00:19.750 --> 00:22.750
I-I thought to myself: "There
must be something better."

00:22.800 --> 00:25.600
And since there wasn't,
I created my own.

00:25.650 --> 00:27.450
We are so lucky
to have you here today...

00:27.500 --> 00:29.050
- Oh, thank you.
- ...to talk about your

00:29.100 --> 00:31.150
best-selling line of fragrances:
Pheromone.

00:31.200 --> 00:33.300
- Indeed.
- Now, I read somewhere

00:33.350 --> 00:34.750
- that you have sold...
- Oh, dear.

00:34.800 --> 00:36.600
...so many bottles
that they now call you

00:36.650 --> 00:38.300
the Queen of Perfume.

00:38.350 --> 00:41.650
They-they do,
but I started from nothing.

00:41.700 --> 00:44.600
Just an idea, and a longing to explore

00:44.650 --> 00:47.800
what perfume is truly about.

00:47.850 --> 00:50.150
What is that? Tell our viewers.

00:50.200 --> 00:53.650
Perfume is about our bodies

00:53.700 --> 00:57.500
talking to each other without words.

00:57.550 --> 00:59.300
LEE [on recording]: You've
reached the Miglins.

00:59.350 --> 01:02.150
Lee? I don't know where you are.

01:02.200 --> 01:07.050
I'm still at the airport,
but I can't wait any longer.

01:09.000 --> 01:11.500
I-I'm gonna catch a taxi.

01:11.550 --> 01:14.700
[woman speaking indistinctly over P.A.]

01:19.850 --> 01:22.650
[sports talk show host
speaking indistinctly on radio]

01:22.700 --> 01:25.200
His fielding percentage
is always at the top,

01:25.250 --> 01:26.500
- so we're expecting...
- [car door closes]

01:33.150 --> 01:35.150
[crow cawing]

01:52.900 --> 01:55.600
Lee?

01:55.650 --> 01:58.150
_

02:12.350 --> 02:13.950
Marilyn?

02:15.700 --> 02:18.300
Something's wrong.

02:34.850 --> 02:38.850
Wait outside. Call the police.

02:41.400 --> 02:43.800
Lee?

03:11.550 --> 03:13.550
♪

03:24.900 --> 03:26.900
[door creaks]

03:42.100 --> 03:44.300
[sirens approaching]

03:53.100 --> 03:54.400
Did you check the garage?

03:54.450 --> 03:56.550
I'll go.

04:00.200 --> 04:03.150
It's right here.

04:11.950 --> 04:13.300
Wait here.

04:31.150 --> 04:33.100
Their Lexus is missing.

04:37.950 --> 04:40.250
[Barbara screaming]

04:48.250 --> 04:50.250
[gasps]

04:54.500 --> 04:56.750
[whispering]: I knew it.

04:57.750 --> 05:02.750
<b>sync and corrected by o-o
www.addic7ed.com</b>

05:08.910 --> 05:12.210
_

05:14.710 --> 05:16.610
_

05:16.660 --> 05:18.560
[indistinct chatter]

05:18.610 --> 05:21.310
[Marilyn laughing]

05:21.360 --> 05:23.560
Well, Lee and I have always been

05:23.610 --> 05:26.210
very interested in education.

05:26.260 --> 05:30.660
And so the idea was that
we would offer aspiring women

05:30.710 --> 05:33.210
at the beginning of their careers

05:33.260 --> 05:36.060
a mentor in their chosen field.

05:36.110 --> 05:37.610
Have you two always been so involved

05:37.660 --> 05:38.760
in each other's lives?

05:38.810 --> 05:41.760
Oh, my goodne... [laughs]

05:41.810 --> 05:43.960
Lee helped me paint my first boutique.

05:44.010 --> 05:45.810
110 East Oak Street.

05:45.860 --> 05:48.110
[laughs] And I wouldn't be
where I am today

05:48.160 --> 05:49.410
without Marilyn.

05:49.460 --> 05:52.310
I-I can't imagine where I would be.

05:52.360 --> 05:55.310
Certainly not at a table like
this, that's for sure.

05:55.360 --> 05:56.910
- Not true.
- I'm honored to call you my friends,

05:56.960 --> 05:58.960
and not too displeased to having you

05:59.010 --> 06:00.560
raise funds for me, either.

06:00.610 --> 06:02.610
She's the one. She's the one.

06:02.660 --> 06:05.660
Please, don't ever decide
to run against me.

06:05.710 --> 06:09.160
Now that you mention it...

06:09.210 --> 06:10.860
[laughter]

06:10.910 --> 06:12.260
MARILYN: So often we are told

06:12.310 --> 06:14.560
that the American Dream is dead.

06:14.610 --> 06:19.710
Except, I say, look at my husband Lee.

06:19.760 --> 06:24.660
One of seven children, the son
of an Illinois coal miner.

06:24.710 --> 06:27.210
He began his career selling

06:27.260 --> 06:29.560
premixed pancake batter

06:29.610 --> 06:33.160
- out of the trunk of a beat-up old car.
- [laughter]

06:33.210 --> 06:38.210
And today, Lee manages
32 million square feet

06:38.260 --> 06:41.460
of commercial property
across the Midwest.

06:41.510 --> 06:44.060
He built the Chicago Bar
Association building,

06:44.110 --> 06:47.060
the 45-story Madison Plaza,

06:47.110 --> 06:49.510
the global headquarters of Hyatt,

06:49.560 --> 06:54.910
and as if that wasn't enough,

06:54.960 --> 06:58.410
he helped me achieve my dreams.

06:58.460 --> 07:02.410
He is my partner

07:02.460 --> 07:05.210
in every sense of the word.

07:05.260 --> 07:07.460
And he is so much more than that.

07:07.510 --> 07:09.960
He is an incredible father,

07:10.010 --> 07:13.060
a perfect husband,

07:13.110 --> 07:17.060
and I'm so proud to say,
without a hint of cynicism,

07:17.110 --> 07:21.460
that my Lee is the American Dream.

07:21.510 --> 07:23.960
Ladies and gentlemen, Lee Miglin.

07:24.010 --> 07:26.010
[applause]

07:31.310 --> 07:33.610
[Lee speaks indistinctly]

07:33.660 --> 07:35.710
MARILYN: And he's funny, too.

07:35.760 --> 07:37.460
[laughter]

07:37.510 --> 07:39.560
LEE [laughs]: Tha-Thank you, Marilyn.

07:39.610 --> 07:42.110
Thank you, folks.
Thank you all for being here.

07:45.410 --> 07:47.710
That went well, I think.

07:47.760 --> 07:51.410
- Very well.
- Mm. And...

07:51.460 --> 07:54.260
I really appreciated your introduction.

07:54.310 --> 07:55.460
I wasn't expecting that.

08:01.310 --> 08:05.710
Do you remember what color
we painted the Oak Street store?

08:05.760 --> 08:08.010
What color? [chuckles]

08:08.060 --> 08:11.460
That was years ago.

08:11.510 --> 08:14.910
We painted it pink.

08:21.510 --> 08:22.910
[sighs]

08:50.760 --> 08:53.760
♪

09:10.860 --> 09:13.060
[phone ringing]

09:13.110 --> 09:14.310
This is Lee.

09:14.360 --> 09:16.510
It's Andrew.

09:16.560 --> 09:18.860
I'm gonna be in Chicago
a couple of days.

09:18.910 --> 09:21.960
C-Can you hold on a moment?

09:34.010 --> 09:35.860
Go on.

09:55.910 --> 09:58.910
♪

10:10.160 --> 10:11.910
MARILYN: Lee, are you home?

10:11.960 --> 10:13.560
LEE: Yes.

10:16.160 --> 10:18.910
What are your plans while I'm away?

10:18.960 --> 10:23.610
Oh, well, I, uh... I need
to finish your accounts.

10:23.660 --> 10:27.460
I'll have them done
by the time you're back.

10:27.510 --> 10:32.060
And I'll... I'll catch up with Paul...

10:32.110 --> 10:34.910
and, uh, go to the, uh,

10:34.960 --> 10:36.760
go to the office.

10:36.810 --> 10:41.460
I will... [sighs]

10:41.510 --> 10:44.710
I'm gonna work, Marilyn.

10:44.760 --> 10:46.760
[sighs] I'm going to work.

10:46.810 --> 10:48.410
That's what I do.

10:48.460 --> 10:50.810
Isn't that what I always do?

10:54.810 --> 10:56.810
What is it?

10:58.160 --> 11:00.110
If you're in one of your blue moods,

11:00.160 --> 11:02.510
why-why don't you come with me?

11:02.560 --> 11:05.760
I like it when you're there.

11:05.810 --> 11:08.160
You do?

11:08.210 --> 11:10.210
Of course.

11:14.410 --> 11:16.960
I'm very proud of you.

11:17.010 --> 11:19.810
You know that, don't you?

11:19.860 --> 11:25.310
I... I could never stand
in front of those cameras.

11:25.360 --> 11:27.960
Well, do you want
to come with me or not?

11:30.360 --> 11:33.660
No. I'm-I'm, I'm being silly.

11:33.710 --> 11:37.110
Well, come on. We'll be late.

11:37.160 --> 11:38.260
Here.

11:38.310 --> 11:40.210
Oh, thank you.

11:50.060 --> 11:52.060
♪

12:17.760 --> 12:19.710
♪ Look out the window ♪

12:19.760 --> 12:23.510
♪ When that rain storms ♪

12:23.560 --> 12:25.860
♪ I let the wind blow up ♪

12:25.910 --> 12:29.710
♪ A brainstorm ♪

12:29.760 --> 12:31.510
♪ And now I'm wondering ♪

12:31.560 --> 12:34.910
♪ Whether weather like this ♪

12:34.960 --> 12:38.610
♪ Gets you, too ♪

12:43.160 --> 12:48.960
♪ It may go on like this for hours ♪

12:49.010 --> 12:54.810
♪ Too late in fall for April showers ♪

12:54.860 --> 12:57.910
♪ So what we got here ♪

12:57.960 --> 13:00.910
♪ Got a thought or two ♪

13:00.960 --> 13:06.410
♪ I need to share with you ♪

13:06.460 --> 13:11.160
♪ Here goes ♪

13:23.260 --> 13:25.110
[door creaks]

13:54.510 --> 13:57.510
♪

14:04.360 --> 14:05.410
[sighs]

14:10.160 --> 14:11.660
I try.

14:14.460 --> 14:17.060
[quavering]: I try.

14:33.910 --> 14:35.960
[car doors lock]

15:05.760 --> 15:07.210
[knocking on door]

15:22.060 --> 15:23.810
[sighs]

15:23.860 --> 15:25.410
[knocking on door]

15:32.310 --> 15:33.610
Come in. Come in.

15:38.410 --> 15:39.460
Andrew.

15:53.130 --> 15:56.430
I didn't expect you to be in town.

15:58.730 --> 16:01.080
Neither did I.

16:01.130 --> 16:03.130
What brings you to Chicago?

16:06.930 --> 16:08.280
Work.

16:08.330 --> 16:09.330
Hmm.

16:16.480 --> 16:19.880
Next time, a little warning
would be useful.

16:19.930 --> 16:22.180
It's sheer luck I have
the house to myself.

16:22.230 --> 16:23.830
When does Marilyn get back?

16:23.880 --> 16:24.930
Sunday morning.

16:26.880 --> 16:28.880
We have some time.

16:28.930 --> 16:30.930
Can you stay the night?

16:34.980 --> 16:37.030
Can you shut the blinds?

16:41.830 --> 16:45.280
I have wanted to share this with you

16:45.330 --> 16:48.880
a long time,

16:48.930 --> 16:51.180
and never had a chance.

16:53.630 --> 16:57.580
♪ It's magic ♪

16:57.630 --> 17:03.430
♪ Without a golden wand ♪

17:05.280 --> 17:07.829
The Skyneedle.

17:13.430 --> 17:14.880
When it's completed,

17:14.930 --> 17:18.480
it will be the tallest
building in the world.

17:18.530 --> 17:20.079
Right here in Chicago.

17:20.130 --> 17:23.829
125 stories.

17:23.880 --> 17:27.780
1,952 feet.

17:27.829 --> 17:28.930
Is it one of yours?

17:28.980 --> 17:31.530
It's my... my pride,

17:31.580 --> 17:33.280
my passion.

17:33.330 --> 17:36.430
Oh, you're building it
just a few blocks away

17:36.480 --> 17:38.330
from Sears Tower.

17:38.380 --> 17:41.680
And taller by 500 feet.

17:41.730 --> 17:43.530
And there's an observation deck?

17:43.580 --> 17:44.780
Of course.

17:44.830 --> 17:46.580
Wait, so...

17:46.630 --> 17:50.330
So you can look down on the
Sears Tower observation deck?

17:50.380 --> 17:51.880
You're gonna put them out of business.

17:51.930 --> 17:54.180
Why would you want to be down there

17:54.230 --> 17:56.130
when you could be up here?

17:56.180 --> 17:58.580
[chuckles] I never thought
of it like that.

18:00.730 --> 18:02.880
Please, that's exactly
how you thought of it.

18:05.030 --> 18:08.330
I imagined riding up
in the elevator with those--

18:08.380 --> 18:11.830
get to the top with
all those families and children

18:11.880 --> 18:13.280
all excited about the view,

18:13.330 --> 18:14.780
excited about being at the top

18:14.830 --> 18:17.730
of the tallest tower in the world.

18:17.780 --> 18:19.730
They wouldn't know who I was.

18:19.780 --> 18:23.730
I could just roam
among them, eavesdropping.

18:26.030 --> 18:29.530
But it's never going to happen?

18:29.580 --> 18:30.930
No, it-it-it...

18:30.980 --> 18:33.380
I promise you this will happen.

18:33.430 --> 18:36.230
Have you broken ground?

18:36.280 --> 18:38.030
Not yet.

18:38.080 --> 18:41.330
♪ It's magic... ♪

18:41.380 --> 18:43.430
And the financing?

18:43.480 --> 18:44.930
No.

18:48.580 --> 18:49.930
The Miglin Tower.

18:49.980 --> 18:51.530
I-I-I told you what it's called.

18:51.580 --> 18:53.880
What's wrong with the Miglin Tower?

18:53.930 --> 18:56.530
It's the Skyneedle.

18:56.580 --> 18:58.930
I-I want it to inspire
people to reach up.

18:58.980 --> 19:02.780
It's about that, not about me.

19:02.830 --> 19:04.630
Of course it's about you.

19:04.680 --> 19:07.680
It's the...

19:07.730 --> 19:09.930
It's the tallest building in the world.

19:09.980 --> 19:11.880
It's the Lee Miglin Tower.

19:11.930 --> 19:15.080
It... it's not about that.

19:15.130 --> 19:17.180
Then what are you
showing this to me for?

19:17.230 --> 19:18.730
Do you think I really want
to spend all evening

19:18.780 --> 19:20.780
listening to how great you are?

19:20.830 --> 19:23.380
A great man with a great tower.

19:23.430 --> 19:26.480
The modest Lee Miglin Tower
inspiring wide-eyed children

19:26.530 --> 19:28.680
for thousands of years to come.

19:28.730 --> 19:31.380
Is that what you think I want to do?

19:31.430 --> 19:35.230
We don't have to talk.

19:35.280 --> 19:37.430
No, we don't.

19:40.180 --> 19:42.180
I understand what you're doing.

19:44.280 --> 19:46.930
You're trying to impress me.

19:46.980 --> 19:49.380
Trying to pretend that this
isn't merely about money.

19:49.430 --> 19:51.930
That this isn't merely
a business transaction.

19:51.980 --> 19:54.280
That there's a genuine
attraction between us.

19:54.330 --> 19:56.980
You can pretend, too, Andrew.

20:07.730 --> 20:09.730
[moaning]

20:12.330 --> 20:14.330
[shudders]

20:15.730 --> 20:17.930
You've never been kissed
like that, have you?

20:17.980 --> 20:19.830
No.

20:19.880 --> 20:20.980
[quietly]: No.

20:21.030 --> 20:23.280
How did it feel?

20:23.330 --> 20:26.580
Feels like I'm alive.

20:26.630 --> 20:29.530
Escorts don't normally kiss, do they?

20:29.580 --> 20:31.780
- No, you're not like...
- Most escorts, no.

20:31.830 --> 20:35.830
I am not like most escorts.
I am not like most anybody.

20:38.130 --> 20:42.530
I could almost be...

20:42.580 --> 20:44.030
a husband.

20:44.080 --> 20:47.130
Or a partner.

20:47.180 --> 20:49.430
I could almost be.

20:49.480 --> 20:51.930
I really could, almost.

20:51.980 --> 20:53.380
I...

20:53.430 --> 20:57.280
I know it's not real, Andrew.
I'm not a fool.

20:57.330 --> 20:59.480
But...

20:59.530 --> 21:02.630
you make it seem so real.

21:06.230 --> 21:07.630
Good.

21:12.080 --> 21:14.380
[whispering]: Let's go out.

21:14.430 --> 21:16.580
- Where are we going?
- To make a mess.

21:16.630 --> 21:18.630
And I don't want you to worry about it.

21:23.230 --> 21:24.630
Come on.

21:28.280 --> 21:30.530
I'm in control now.

21:35.530 --> 21:37.080
Ah-ah.

21:37.130 --> 21:38.530
Ah...

21:38.580 --> 21:40.580
Oh...

21:41.880 --> 21:44.330
[muffled moans]

21:54.480 --> 21:56.130
[Andrew panting]

22:18.730 --> 22:19.680
Yeah. Down.

22:19.730 --> 22:22.430
[Lee grunting]

22:22.480 --> 22:23.780
Yeah.

22:27.980 --> 22:31.930
So... dominant out there.

22:33.680 --> 22:35.630
So submissive in here.

22:35.680 --> 22:38.230
So powerful out there.

22:38.280 --> 22:40.680
- So pathetic...
- [grunts]

22:40.730 --> 22:42.280
...in here.

22:42.330 --> 22:44.530
But you like being pathetic, don't you?

22:53.130 --> 22:55.330
- Yeah.
- [grunts]

22:55.380 --> 22:56.680
Yeah.

23:03.730 --> 23:04.980
[groaning]

23:10.880 --> 23:12.380
[gasping]

23:15.880 --> 23:17.730
[muffled groans]

23:20.380 --> 23:23.280
I've killed two people, Lee.

23:23.330 --> 23:26.280
Two people that were very close to me.

23:26.330 --> 23:28.780
I know it's hard to believe.

23:28.830 --> 23:31.780
Intellectual Andrew.

23:31.830 --> 23:33.380
Well-read, well-spoken Andrew.

23:33.430 --> 23:35.180
Well-dressed.

23:39.180 --> 23:42.830
But here I am.

23:42.880 --> 23:44.880
This is me.

23:48.080 --> 23:50.880
Now, I know that you're not

23:50.930 --> 23:53.130
wearing your hearing aid,

23:53.180 --> 23:54.480
so I'm going to speak

23:54.530 --> 23:57.830
very loudly and very clearly

23:57.880 --> 24:00.480
- so you can understand.
- [muffled groaning]

24:00.530 --> 24:02.730
I want you to know that
when they find your body,

24:02.780 --> 24:05.430
you will be wearing ladies' panties...

24:07.180 --> 24:10.230
surrounded by gay porn.

24:10.280 --> 24:15.030
I want the world to see...

24:15.080 --> 24:17.330
that the great Lee Miglin

24:17.380 --> 24:20.030
is a sissy.

24:21.730 --> 24:24.830
Soon, the whole world will know
that the great Lee Miglin,

24:24.880 --> 24:28.730
who built Chicago,
built it with a limp wrist.

24:30.630 --> 24:32.330
The cops will know.

24:32.380 --> 24:34.380
The press will know.
Your wife will know.

24:34.430 --> 24:36.930
Your children will know.
The neighbors will know.

24:36.980 --> 24:38.530
Tell me something, Lee,

24:38.580 --> 24:42.280
what terrifies you more,
death or being disgraced?

24:42.330 --> 24:45.330
[muffled crying]

24:45.380 --> 24:47.930
Disgraced.

24:47.980 --> 24:50.480
You know, disgrace isn't that bad.

24:53.580 --> 24:55.230
Once you settle into it.

25:01.430 --> 25:02.680
Disgrace.

25:07.280 --> 25:09.280
[muffled groaning]

25:13.030 --> 25:15.730
[Andrew grunts]

25:15.780 --> 25:18.580
Concrete can build.

25:18.630 --> 25:22.880
Concrete can kill.

25:24.680 --> 25:26.230
[grunts]

25:26.280 --> 25:28.280
[panting]

25:53.030 --> 25:55.030
[insects chirping]

26:19.080 --> 26:21.080
♪

26:52.960 --> 26:54.910
[siren wailing]

26:54.960 --> 26:56.960
[indistinct radio transmission]

27:10.060 --> 27:12.510
JOURNALIST: Superintendent!

27:12.560 --> 27:14.460
Superintendent, was there a robbery?

27:14.510 --> 27:15.810
[journalists clamoring]

27:15.860 --> 27:18.460
And did Lee Miglin know the intruder?

27:18.510 --> 27:20.510
[camera shutter clicks]

27:21.860 --> 27:23.910
RODRIGUEZ: Carry on.

27:32.910 --> 27:34.360
The underwear?

27:34.410 --> 27:35.960
Was he wearing them at the time
of his death,

27:36.010 --> 27:37.160
or dressed afterwards?

27:37.210 --> 27:39.110
I can't be sure.

27:39.160 --> 27:40.310
Defensive wounds?

27:40.360 --> 27:41.510
None.

27:41.560 --> 27:44.310
No cuts or bruises to his hands,

27:44.360 --> 27:47.160
but his ribs?

27:47.210 --> 27:49.360
Every single rib is broken.

27:50.760 --> 27:52.860
I don't want any details leaking.

27:52.910 --> 27:54.060
Make that understood.

27:54.110 --> 27:56.310
Yes, sir.

27:56.360 --> 27:59.960
We confirm only: "An elderly
gentleman has been killed."

28:02.110 --> 28:04.010
- PAUL: Marilyn.
- Hmm?

28:04.060 --> 28:08.310
I swear to you, this had nothing
to do with his business.

28:08.360 --> 28:09.660
His business?

28:09.710 --> 28:11.510
We all know that.

28:11.560 --> 28:14.260
I've been through the entire
contents of the house.

28:14.310 --> 28:16.110
It was a robbery, no question.

28:16.160 --> 28:18.760
Aside from the Lexus, a great
deal of money was stolen.

28:18.810 --> 28:21.860
While I was away, Lee's
secretary delivered $2,000.

28:21.910 --> 28:24.210
That's missing,
along with two leather coats,

28:24.260 --> 28:27.510
two suits, some inconsequential
pieces of jewelry--

28:27.560 --> 28:28.760
uh, Lee had gold coins.

28:28.810 --> 28:30.360
He gave them as gifts.

28:30.410 --> 28:32.560
They are unusual,
and should be easy to trace,

28:32.610 --> 28:35.010
should the culprit try to pawn them.

28:35.060 --> 28:40.410
And, um, a dozen pairs
of new Sulka black socks.

28:41.910 --> 28:43.860
Aren't you going to write this down?

28:43.910 --> 28:45.410
I'll have an officer take
your statement.

28:45.460 --> 28:48.560
Marilyn, this is
Superintendent Rodriguez.

28:48.610 --> 28:50.560
I know who he is.

28:50.610 --> 28:53.810
I happen to be friends with
a great many police officers.

28:53.860 --> 28:57.310
Do you think I called 911 earlier? No.

28:57.360 --> 28:59.710
I called Commander Ettore DiVito,

28:59.760 --> 29:01.710
who was present at the
Wallenberg Award celebration

29:01.760 --> 29:04.460
a few weeks ago, and asked
to speak to him directly.

29:04.510 --> 29:07.060
We're all here for you.

29:07.110 --> 29:09.460
Lee was alone.

29:09.510 --> 29:11.860
In the house.

29:11.910 --> 29:15.210
He was vulnerable.

29:15.260 --> 29:19.010
It was an opportunistic attack.

29:19.060 --> 29:21.460
He wears a hearing aid, did you know?

29:21.510 --> 29:23.660
- No, I didn't.
- Well, the burglar could have

29:23.710 --> 29:26.910
easily surprised him.

29:26.960 --> 29:29.910
Poor Lee, he wouldn't have
had a... chance.

29:29.960 --> 29:31.310
He wouldn't have fought back.

29:31.360 --> 29:34.910
Mrs. Miglin, maybe we can talk
at another time.

29:34.960 --> 29:37.360
Talk now. Why not?

29:37.410 --> 29:41.260
There were certain items

29:41.310 --> 29:44.060
beside your husband's body.

29:44.110 --> 29:45.810
What items?

29:45.860 --> 29:48.610
Pornographic magazines.

29:48.660 --> 29:51.660
Homosexual pornographic magazines.

29:51.710 --> 29:53.760
I see.

29:55.360 --> 29:57.710
Well, they must belong to the killer.

29:57.760 --> 30:00.760
It would mean he brought
the magazines in with him.

30:02.160 --> 30:06.410
I'm not interested in his intentions.

30:06.460 --> 30:08.860
Find him. Catch him.

30:08.910 --> 30:11.460
But don't talk to me
about what might or might not

30:11.510 --> 30:13.860
be going through his mind.

30:13.910 --> 30:15.910
I understand.

30:18.410 --> 30:21.860
The killer took a bath and shaved?

30:21.910 --> 30:24.710
Yeah. He might've stayed the night.

30:35.410 --> 30:39.260
He must've known
Marilyn was coming home.

30:42.760 --> 30:44.760
Where did you get those?

30:50.860 --> 30:54.160
Mrs. Miglin.

30:54.210 --> 30:55.860
It's very thoughtful of you,

30:55.910 --> 30:57.660
but there is really no need
to buy my men food.

30:57.710 --> 30:59.310
Oh, I didn't buy it.

30:59.360 --> 31:00.610
It was donated.

31:00.660 --> 31:03.410
By Gibsons Steakhouse on Rush Street.

31:03.460 --> 31:05.860
They're friends of the family.
They wanted to help.

31:05.910 --> 31:07.860
I'm sorry, we haven't been introduced.

31:07.910 --> 31:10.210
Oh, this is Duke, my son.

31:10.260 --> 31:12.260
I'm Superintendent Rodriguez.

31:12.310 --> 31:13.560
Sorry for your loss.

31:13.610 --> 31:15.760
Duke's flown in from California.

31:15.810 --> 31:17.010
He's a Hollywood actor.

31:17.060 --> 31:18.210
Aspiring to be.

31:18.260 --> 31:20.360
No-- no, well, you've had roles.

31:20.410 --> 31:21.710
Good roles.

31:21.760 --> 31:23.560
Tell him about the film you're in.

31:23.610 --> 31:25.360
Air Force One.

31:25.410 --> 31:26.560
It's going to be released this summer.

31:26.610 --> 31:28.710
Yeah, starring Harrison Ford.

31:28.760 --> 31:30.110
Coming out July 25.

31:30.160 --> 31:31.260
Mm-hmm.

31:31.310 --> 31:32.960
He plays a pilot.

31:33.010 --> 31:34.860
A-a Russian pilot.

31:34.910 --> 31:37.710
There are lots of pilots in the movie.

31:37.760 --> 31:40.960
He's at the beginning of a great career.

32:01.360 --> 32:03.360
[dog barking in distance]

32:09.760 --> 32:13.260
Squad, I want to run
a license check for Minnesota,

32:13.310 --> 32:14.960
5-4-3,

32:15.010 --> 32:17.960
Lincoln, Union, George.

32:18.010 --> 32:21.610
DISPATCHER: 10-4. Minnesota,
5-4-3, Lincoln, Union, George.

32:21.660 --> 32:23.360
[radio crackles]

32:23.410 --> 32:25.160
We've got a hit.

32:25.210 --> 32:28.660
Vehicle reported stolen, linked
to the homicide of Jeff Trail.

32:31.460 --> 32:33.310
What do you have?

32:33.360 --> 32:36.860
Lee Miglin's car is fitted with a phone.

32:36.910 --> 32:38.660
But the killer's not gonna be
stupid enough to use it.

32:38.710 --> 32:40.010
He couldn't, even if he wanted to.

32:40.060 --> 32:41.160
It's locked with a numerical code.

32:41.210 --> 32:43.110
Okay. So?

32:43.160 --> 32:45.010
So the phone turns on
when the ignition turns on.

32:45.060 --> 32:46.810
Regardless of whether
he's using it or not.

32:46.860 --> 32:49.410
We got two pings.
One at 11:25 Saturday night,

32:49.460 --> 32:52.260
and again, at 12:37, Sunday morning.

32:52.310 --> 32:54.360
Now, the Saturday night signal
was transmitted from a tower

32:54.410 --> 32:56.860
located in Grand Rapids, Michigan.

32:56.910 --> 32:59.460
The Sunday morning one
from Union County, Pennsylvania.

32:59.510 --> 33:01.360
He's heading to New York.

33:01.410 --> 33:04.260
His phone's talking to us,
and he doesn't even know it.

33:04.310 --> 33:06.710
Who else has this?

33:06.760 --> 33:08.860
- Just the FBI and us.
- I want this kept between

33:08.910 --> 33:10.660
as few people as possible.

33:10.710 --> 33:12.110
No matter what he does next,
wherever he goes...

33:12.160 --> 33:14.160
We got him.

33:15.860 --> 33:17.060
[door opens]

33:25.380 --> 33:27.380
["St. Thomas" by Sonny Rollins playing]

33:50.180 --> 33:52.630
♪

34:09.130 --> 34:11.179
[table screeching]

34:36.130 --> 34:38.130
♪

34:56.929 --> 35:01.430
Does the name Andrew Cunanan
mean anything to you?

35:01.480 --> 35:03.430
No.

35:03.480 --> 35:05.430
Nothing.

35:05.480 --> 35:06.780
Who is he?

35:06.830 --> 35:08.580
He worked as an escort.

35:08.630 --> 35:11.030
He's wanted in connection
with the murder of two men.

35:11.080 --> 35:13.430
The first in Minneapolis,
the second in Chisago.

35:13.480 --> 35:15.830
- In Minnesota.
- What does this have to do with Lee?

35:15.880 --> 35:17.880
Cunanan stole a jeep

35:17.930 --> 35:19.480
from his second victim.

35:19.530 --> 35:22.230
That jeep was found parked
on Astor Street.

35:22.280 --> 35:24.280
A block away from this house.

35:26.530 --> 35:29.630
I've never seen this man before.

35:30.830 --> 35:33.580
You understand this investigation

35:33.630 --> 35:36.580
is no longer contained
within the Chicago police force?

35:36.630 --> 35:39.430
The FBI is leading a nationwide manhunt.

35:39.480 --> 35:41.130
All we care about, Superintendent,

35:41.180 --> 35:44.380
is that you find the man
responsible for Lee's murder.

36:03.330 --> 36:07.130
An Ameritech cell phone tracking
tower reported a signal at 1:30,

36:07.180 --> 36:08.930
and another one at 3:00.

36:08.980 --> 36:10.780
He's on the move.

36:10.830 --> 36:15.430
Both the Philadelphia police
and the FBI are closing in.

36:17.880 --> 36:19.880
I hope they're ready.

36:22.980 --> 36:25.180
MARILYN: I know what they're saying.

36:25.230 --> 36:27.530
About me.

36:27.580 --> 36:29.030
[door closes]

36:29.080 --> 36:31.230
"Why hasn't she cried?"

36:31.280 --> 36:33.980
"Where's the grief? The emotion?"

36:34.030 --> 36:35.980
"She couldn't have loved him."

36:36.030 --> 36:39.280
"How could a woman who cares
so much about appearance

36:39.330 --> 36:41.680
appear not to care?"

36:41.730 --> 36:45.530
Eh, people say all kinds of...
nasty things.

36:45.580 --> 36:48.780
- Even at a time like this.
- Especially at a time like this.

36:51.130 --> 36:53.130
When you're weak.

36:55.130 --> 36:57.130
When you're down.

37:01.030 --> 37:04.130
How dare they say
our marriage was a sham?

37:04.180 --> 37:07.280
Lee and I...

37:07.330 --> 37:09.530
shared our whole lives.

37:11.430 --> 37:15.580
We... shared all kinds of adventures.

37:15.630 --> 37:18.880
We rode in hot air balloons.

37:18.930 --> 37:21.730
When I was lost in the desert...

37:24.080 --> 37:26.480
[voice breaking]: ...he rescued me.

37:28.280 --> 37:32.030
How many couples can say they
have that k-kind of romance?

37:32.080 --> 37:34.080
I...

37:36.080 --> 37:38.480
[crying]: ...loved him.

37:41.930 --> 37:45.230
[crying]: I loved him...

37:45.280 --> 37:47.280
very much.

37:56.330 --> 37:58.030
[Marilyn sniffles]

37:58.080 --> 38:02.880
There. Is that better?

38:02.930 --> 38:05.230
Am I a real wife now?

38:05.280 --> 38:07.680
[panting]

38:09.180 --> 38:11.630
[Marilyn sniffles]

38:14.830 --> 38:18.180
[chuckles softly]

38:18.230 --> 38:21.130
We had a fairy-tale life.

38:25.430 --> 38:28.880
We didn't even fight.

38:28.930 --> 38:32.580
He didn't raise a finger.

38:36.980 --> 38:39.330
But I will.

38:47.330 --> 38:49.730
It was a robbery.

38:51.730 --> 38:53.730
And a random killing.

39:04.580 --> 39:07.030
Local radio, KYW News,
is running a story

39:07.080 --> 39:09.630
that Lee Miglin's car phone
had been activated

39:09.680 --> 39:12.080
and we're tracking the signal.

39:16.080 --> 39:17.530
[shouts]

39:30.050 --> 39:31.650
MAN [on radio]: Find out if that
trend will continue through

39:31.700 --> 39:35.000
the weekend. The forecast
is coming up after the news.

39:35.050 --> 39:36.300
An update on the Miglin murder.

39:36.350 --> 39:38.050
We're hearing reports

39:38.100 --> 39:40.600
that Lee Miglin's car phone
was activated on Thursday,

39:40.650 --> 39:43.100
which means authorities
can now track the movements

39:43.150 --> 39:44.550
of the stolen car.

39:44.600 --> 39:46.350
Nothing further has been confirmed.

39:46.400 --> 39:48.850
Of course, we'll keep you up
to date with the very latest.

39:48.900 --> 39:50.850
After the break,
we'll have a detailed account

39:50.900 --> 39:52.650
on your weather through the weekend,

39:52.700 --> 39:55.300
as well as further updates on traffic.

39:57.800 --> 39:59.050
[tires screech]

39:59.100 --> 40:01.100
[car horn blares]

40:10.100 --> 40:12.100
[grunting]

40:30.750 --> 40:32.550
[engine starts]

40:32.600 --> 40:34.600
[tires screeching]

40:48.300 --> 40:50.300
[tires screeching]

40:51.050 --> 40:54.400
_

40:54.450 --> 40:56.550
♪

41:08.650 --> 41:10.600
WOMAN: All right, you all set, hon?

41:10.650 --> 41:12.650
[people chattering quietly]

41:20.750 --> 41:23.600
♪

41:41.600 --> 41:43.600
[engine starts]

41:51.500 --> 41:53.500
♪

42:13.350 --> 42:15.350
[man coughs]

42:16.550 --> 42:18.400
[zips bag]

42:18.450 --> 42:20.450
[vehicle approaching]

42:25.450 --> 42:27.450
[engine idling]

42:34.200 --> 42:36.600
- [car door closes]
- [engine starts]

42:47.150 --> 42:49.150
♪

43:16.850 --> 43:18.850
[engine stops]

43:46.450 --> 43:48.850
[sighs]

43:49.900 --> 43:51.650
[music playing over radio]

43:51.700 --> 43:54.350
♪ I told you I was leaving my job... ♪

43:54.400 --> 43:55.900
[footsteps approaching]

43:55.950 --> 43:57.450
[door opens]

43:59.450 --> 44:01.800
- [door closes]
- Stay calm.

44:01.850 --> 44:04.450
No one's gonna get hurt.

44:04.500 --> 44:07.500
I'm here to steal your truck.

44:07.550 --> 44:09.550
Where are the keys?

44:09.600 --> 44:13.150
Wait. Uh, leave them there. Leave them.

44:13.200 --> 44:15.350
Get away from the desk.

44:19.200 --> 44:21.800
Is... is there a downstairs?

44:21.850 --> 44:24.050
Basement.

44:24.100 --> 44:27.000
Can I lock you in there?

44:27.050 --> 44:29.850
Door's got a lock. Yes, sir.

44:39.600 --> 44:42.050
Get on your knees.

44:46.250 --> 44:48.650
Sir...

44:48.700 --> 44:52.050
if you're thinking
of killing me, please hear this.

44:52.100 --> 44:54.650
I'm a married man.

44:54.700 --> 44:57.150
We have a son-- Troy.

44:57.200 --> 44:59.750
And, sir, I'd very much
like to see them again.

44:59.800 --> 45:01.800
And I'd be grateful if you'd let me...

45:16.000 --> 45:18.000
♪

45:46.300 --> 45:48.300
[engine starts]

45:51.000 --> 45:53.000
[tires screeching]

46:02.100 --> 46:04.950
WOMAN: We're live in five, four...

46:05.000 --> 46:08.100
PRESENTER: Marilyn, from your family

46:08.150 --> 46:09.800
here at the Home Shopping Channel,

46:09.850 --> 46:13.200
may I extend our deepest condolences?

46:13.250 --> 46:16.000
Thank you.

46:16.050 --> 46:18.250
For those of you who don't know,

46:18.300 --> 46:20.400
Marilyn's husband was brutally murdered

46:20.450 --> 46:23.150
in a tragic act of random violence.

46:24.900 --> 46:28.550
They killed my husband for a car.

46:28.600 --> 46:31.000
Terrible. It's so terrible.

46:33.000 --> 46:35.450
You have a few words
that you'd like to say.

46:39.650 --> 46:43.100
I... had to think long and hard

46:43.150 --> 46:46.600
before coming back to the show.

46:46.650 --> 46:49.500
In the end,

46:49.550 --> 46:53.450
I believe it's what my husband
would have wanted, you see.

46:53.500 --> 46:57.150
His name is on these bottles, too.

46:59.400 --> 47:01.850
Miglin.

47:01.900 --> 47:05.350
He was my legal counsel,
my accountant, my best friend.

47:05.400 --> 47:07.400
He...

47:12.000 --> 47:14.000
[voice breaking]: He believed in me.

47:16.000 --> 47:19.650
How many husbands believe
in their wives' dreams?

47:19.700 --> 47:24.150
How many... treat us as partners?

47:24.200 --> 47:26.400
As equals?

47:29.950 --> 47:31.950
We...

47:32.000 --> 47:35.550
We were a team...

47:35.600 --> 47:39.550
for 38 years.

47:39.600 --> 47:43.550
And I... miss him very much.

47:44.600 --> 47:48.050
Are you able to go on?

47:48.100 --> 47:51.650
When I first started selling
my perfume on television...

47:51.700 --> 47:53.400
[sniffles]

47:53.450 --> 47:55.500
my friend Dorsey Connors,

47:55.550 --> 47:58.550
who hosted her own television
show, gave me a piece of advice.

47:58.600 --> 48:00.600
And she said,

48:00.650 --> 48:03.900
"Just think of the little red light

48:03.950 --> 48:06.300
as the man you love."

